  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Luminite Drills</b> are four <linked>tools</linked>, all of which have the same stats. The four types are the  <b>Vortex Drill</b>, <b>Nebula Drill</b>, <b>Solar Flare Drill</b>, and the <b>Stardust Drill</b>, each themed after a different <linked>Celestial Pillar</linked>. On <linked>[img:Legacy tModLoader version]</linked><linked> Legacy tModLoader</linked>, they are unobtainable through normal gameplay, so their <linked>pickaxe counterparts</linked> must be crafted instead.",
    "Unlike all other <linked>drills</linked>, Luminite Drills can be reforged with size and speed <linked>modifiers</linked>, but this is made irrelevant by the fact that they cannot benefit from them, thus, a drill with <b>Deadly</b> or <b>Light</b> mines just as fast as one with no modifier.",
    "<span class=\"eico i6\" title=\"Legacy tModLoader version\"><b></b><i></i></span> With current methods, it is impossible to hack these items into a character's inventory using external editors, as they will disappear from that character's inventory as soon as they load into a world.",
    "<span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span> Their best <linked>modifier</linked> is <b>Godly</b> or <b>Demonic</b>. Both modifiers increase the average damage output by the same amount.",
    "<span class=\"eico i3 i5 i6\" title=\"Old-gen console, 3DS and Legacy tModLoader versions\"><b></b><i></i></span> Their best <linked>modifier</linked> is <b>Demonic</b>, as they do not have any knockback and thus cannot get modifiers that affect it, and furthermore cannot get modifiers that affect their speed, either."
  ],
